<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,150,176]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy, 2021" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[322,479,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,479,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Chrysis polita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[486,575,150,176]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[486,575,150,176]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[745,856,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ignita">
<emphasis box="[745,856,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. ignita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. It is related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linsenmaier" authorityYear="1959" box="[1190,1339,150,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castigata">
<emphasis box="[1190,1339,150,176]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. castigata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="du Buysson, 1898 a" authorityName="du Buysson" authorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. immaculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="du Buysson, R." box="[262,478,186,213]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="125 - 147" refId="ref51482" refString="du Buysson, R. (1898 a) Contribution aux Chrysides du Globe (3 e serie). Revue d'Entomologie, 17, 125 - 147." type="journal article" year="1898">du Buysson, 1898a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1854" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" box="[536,862,186,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exsulans">
<emphasis box="[536,678,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. exsulans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dahlbom, A. G." box="[685,862,186,213]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref51020" refString="Dahlbom, A. G. (1854) Hymenoptera Europaea praecipue borealia, formis typicis nonnullis specierum generumve exoticorum propter nexum systematicum associatis, per familias, genera, species et varietates disposita atque descripta. Tomus secundus. Chrysis in sensu Linnaeano. Friedrich Nicolai, Berolini [Berlin], xxiv + 412 pp., 12 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 15890" type="book" year="1854">Dahlbom, 1854</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, for general habitus, genitalia and colouration, with tergum I blue, contrasting with the other two red metasomal terga. 
<taxonomicName authority="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy, 2021" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[910,1069,222,248]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[910,1069,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Chrysis polita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1077,1168,222,248]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1077,1168,222,248]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be easily separated from other similar species for the scattered punctation of the metasomal tergum II (
<figureCitation box="[1092,1195,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 51" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,993,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-375@54.[151,1436,993,1927]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 51. Chrysis metasoma, dorsal view, and genital capsule. A, E. Chrysis polita Rosa, sp. nov. B, F. Chrysis exsulans Dahlbom, 1844. C, G. Chrysis castigata Linsenmaier, 1959. D, H. Chrysis immaculata du Buysson, 1898. Scale bars 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4544702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4544702/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 51A</figureCitation>
) and for the shape of the genital capsule (
<figureCitation box="[375,476,294,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 51" captionStartId="54.[151,250,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,993,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-375@54.[151,1436,993,1927]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="FIGURE 51. Chrysis metasoma, dorsal view, and genital capsule. A, E. Chrysis polita Rosa, sp. nov. B, F. Chrysis exsulans Dahlbom, 1844. C, G. Chrysis castigata Linsenmaier, 1959. D, H. Chrysis immaculata du Buysson, 1898. Scale bars 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4544702" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4544702/files/figure.png" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Fig. 51E</figureCitation>
); moreover, it is separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linsenmaier" authorityYear="1959" box="[838,987,294,320]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castigata">
<emphasis box="[838,987,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. castigata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="du Buysson" authorityYear="1898" box="[1041,1220,294,320]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculata">
<emphasis box="[1041,1220,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. immaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by different colour pattern of the tergum I, which is apically red to golden red, whereas it is fully blue in 
<taxonomicName authority="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy, 2021" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[1129,1242,330,356]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1129,1242,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. polita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1250,1341,330,356]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1250,1341,330,356]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Besides different punctation and genitalia, it is separated from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1854" box="[778,969,366,392]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exsulans">
<emphasis box="[778,969,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Chrysis exsulans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by different shape of tergum III, and its apical teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Another two species have contrasting blue tergum I, the females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1761" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1761" box="[980,1338,438,464]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgida">
<emphasis box="[980,1153,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Chrysis fulgida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[1163,1338,438,464]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref53393" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1761) Fauna Svecica sistens Animalia Sveciae Regni: Mammalia, Aves, Amphibia, Pisces, Insecta, Vermes. Distributa per Classes et Ordines, Genera et Species, cum Differentiis, Specierum, Synonymis, Auctorum, Nominibus Incolarum, Locis natalium, Descriptionibus Insectorum. Editio Altera, Auctior. Laurentius Salvius, Stockholmiae, 578 pp., 2 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 46380" type="book" year="1761">Linnaeus, 1761</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Tsuneki, 1952" authorityName="Tsuneki" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgidaria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. fulgidaria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tsuneki, K." box="[270,432,474,501]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="31 - 33" refId="ref57509" refString="Tsuneki, K. (1952) Two new species of Chrysididae from Japan and Korea. Insecta Matsumurana, 18 (1 - 2), 31 - 33." type="journal article" year="1952">Tsuneki, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The first is a relatively common species in the Palaearctic region but genetically belongs to a different subgroup, together with 
<taxonomicName authority="Christ, 1791" authorityName="Christ" authorityYear="1791" box="[588,824,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iris">
<emphasis box="[588,674,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. iris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Christ, J. L." box="[684,824,510,536]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" refId="ref50781" refString="Christ, J. L. (1791) Naturgeschichte, Klassification und Nomenclatur der Insekten vom Bienen, Wespen und Ameisengeschlecht: als der funften Klasse funfte Ordnung des Linneischen Natursystems von den Insekten, Hymenoptera: mit hautigen Flugeln. Hermannischer Buchhandlung, Frankfurt am Main, 535 pp., 60 pls." type="book" year="1791">Christ, 1791</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pauli, T. &amp; Castillo-Cajas, R. F. &amp; Rosa, P. &amp; Kukowka, S. &amp; Berg, A. &amp; van den Berghe, E. &amp; Fornoff, F. &amp; Hopfenmuller, S. &amp; Niehuis, M. &amp; Peters, R. S. &amp; Staab, M. &amp; Strumia, F. &amp; Tischendorf, S. &amp; Schmitt, F. &amp; Niehuis, O." box="[841,1037,510,536]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" pagination="322 - 335" refId="ref54423" refString="Pauli, T., Castillo-Cajas, R. F., Rosa, P., Kukowka, S., Berg, A., van den Berghe, E., Fornoff, F., Hopfenmuller, S., Niehuis, M., Peters, R. S., Staab, M., Strumia, F., Tischendorf, S., Schmitt, F. &amp; Niehuis, O. (2019) Phylogenetic analysis of cuckoo wasps (Chrysididae) reveals the partially artificial nature of the current classification at the genus level in this family of Hymenoptera. Systematic Entomology, 44 (2), 322 - 335. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12323" type="journal article" year="2019">
Pauli 
<emphasis box="[909,968,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
); besides the morphological differences, the male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1761" box="[369,497,546,572]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgida">
<emphasis box="[369,497,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. fulgida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also differently coloured, having a large blue dorsal spot on tergum II. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tsuneki" authorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulgidaria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Chrysis fulgidaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described on a single female Korean specimen, and it can be easily separated from 
<taxonomicName authority="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy, 2021" authorityName="Rosa &amp; Aswathi &amp; Bijoy" authorityYear="2021" box="[1231,1342,582,608]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1231,1342,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ch. polita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1348,1436,582,608]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1348,1436,582,608]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by dense metasomal punctation and narrow and spine-like apical teeth on tergum III.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
